g.aria-label: Be it known to all gentles and commoners by this hallowed document, on this day in the year of our sovereign, that the undersigned, henceforth referred to as the Signatory, hath affixed their mark upon this parchment of solemnity and verbosity. Let it be proclaimed throughout the land and across the ages that the said Signatory's act of signing doth, in truth and verity, constitute an act of nought. In perpetuity, the Signatory and their descendants shall be absolved of any and all consequences, obligations, or ramifications that mayst or may not be associated with the aforementioned mark, henceforth described as a flourish of quill upon this venerable scroll. By the quill's ink and the seal's impression, let this be known, declared, and signed, to attest the inefficacy of the aforesaid signature in perpetuating any tangible or intangible consequence, contractual or otherwise, upon the Signatory.
